HEADWORD: Staktometer
<hw>Stak*tom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧k*t⟦ocr⟧m"⟦esl⟧*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>stakto`s</grk> falling by drops +
<ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>A drop measurer; a glass tube tapering to
a small orifice at the point, and having a bulb in the middle, used for
finding the number of drops in equal quantities of different liquids.
See <er>Pipette</er>.</def> <rj><au>Sir D. Brewster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stal</ent>⟦br⟧
